00:47:03,589 --> 00:47:07,411
The merit of 2D prototyping is that you can clearly

423
00:47:07,491 --> 00:47:09,253
symbolize the game and build the logic.

424
00:47:09,773 --> 00:47:12,475
2D prototyping is handy in that it allows you

425
00:47:12,515 --> 00:47:14,356
to reduce the game to a set of symbols

426
00:47:14,897 --> 00:47:17,238
and clearly display the logic behind an idea.

427
00:47:23,040 --> 00:47:26,624
As you can see, this prototype is actually in 3D, and under the hood there were early

428
00:47:26,644 --> 00:47:28,286
versions of our physics and chemistry engines at work.

429
00:47:53,651 --> 00:48:00,477
In the world of Breath of the Wild, this multiplicative gameplay is found in the space between situations and goals.

430
00:48:07,103 --> 00:48:14,390
If you can see these connections between elements in the world, the scenery around you takes on new meaning and poses questions to you.

431
00:48:18,193 --> 00:48:22,675
It should also inspire you to experiment and try out all sorts of ideas.

432
00:48:25,156 --> 00:48:27,696
We've filled every corner of the game world with these sets of situations and goals.

433
00:48:27,776 --> 00:48:30,697
And of course, we've envisioned correct ways to solve each of them.

434
00:48:41,813 --> 00:48:45,656
