435
00:48:45,676 --> 00:48:48,679
Instead, we want them to have fun thinking up and trying solutions on their own.

436
00:49:08,188 --> 00:49:10,350
Having listened to our presentation up to this point,

437
00:49:10,630 --> 00:49:13,352
have you found yourselves puzzling out your own answers

438
00:49:13,472 --> 00:49:15,214
to the situations we've shown on screen?

439
00:49:17,816 --> 00:49:20,358
Even if it's a little inefficient or an unexpected shortcut,

440
00:49:20,378 --> 00:49:24,001
as long as you enjoy the experience of thinking, trying, and completing it,

441
00:49:24,021 --> 00:49:26,283
I think that's the right answer to this game.

442
00:49:27,999 --> 00:49:33,425
If thinking up, trying out, and eventually finding roundabout solutions or unexpected

443
00:49:33,485 --> 00:49:38,550
shortcuts is fun, then I think that in itself is the correct way to play this game.

444
00:49:50,277 --> 00:49:53,038
One convention we broke with in making Breath of the Wild

445
00:49:53,358 --> 00:49:56,839
was to create a world where fun occurs through multiplication,

446
00:49:57,319 --> 00:49:59,880
as opposed to one in which fun elements are simply

